    "branch_rationale": "Matter-localised anisotropy diagnostic. The (2+1) sign pattern in the per-axis Lambda spatial trace is identified in the parent paper as matter-localised: at heavy-tail T_00 nodes (matter-rich regions) the per-node anisotropy is large, while at low-T_00 vacuum-like regions it is small. Cross-regime mean Spearman correlation between per-node 2+1 strength and local T_00 magnitude is +0.556 with maximum +0.920 at N=28, confirming the matter-source coupling. Regime range N=28..512 spans the chirality flip; mixing pre-flip and post-flip lattice data is intentional for tracking the finite-N convergence towards isotropy as N grows.",
